  "description": "Two individuals, male and female were loafing/snoozing at a playa amid what looked like corn stubble along CR BB just south of CR 58. Water levels were quite high in the area, and a number of other shorebirds/waterfowl/ibis were in the area. In the immediate surroundings, over 40 Long-billed Dowitchers were feeding and snoozing as well, providing good size comparisons. Despite the suboptimal light, the color patterns on the godwits were easily discernible in the scope. Male & female godwits with slightly decurved bills, white tail bases with black terminal bands. Male with rich brick-red breast, dark back, and pale gray striped head. Female gray overall with white undertail coverts.",
